postcontent:
This gun is sold pending payment.  Images are left for the curious for now.

I do have a 160 and 150 available if a similar gun with sloped grip is desired.  Also, the Steyr FP.

Some other 120 are in testing at this time, and probably will be available in the spring or early summer.  Feel free to contact, if you wish to be notified when they are available.  They will be advertised on Armslist, and probably also Target Talk.

The Hammerli 120 pistols area an extremely accurate single shot pistol in .22lr, using a lateral or side positioned Luger locking system.  

The trigger pull can be adjusted from several lbs down to a few ounces, rendering them suitable as hunting guns, target guns, or free pistols.  Among the free pistols, they are the only ones that were made with a "Colt 1911" style military grip.

The gun is available either with the grip as shown, or with a more combat style (but still right handed) grip with no palm shelf.  

10" barrel, .22lr, made in Germany (as were 99.9% of the 120).

The accuracy of this handgun is better than that of nearly any USA target rifle.  It can be used with any velocity ammunition (CB through ultra-high velocity), extending its utility.  Designed for iron sighs, it also has an 11mm dovetail integral to the gun, for optical sights.

This gun is one of several free pistols available.  For a complete list and EXPERT'S SELECTION GUIDE to these guns, please email.  The guide and list are free.

FFL transfer only.  Please note, in some localities, this gun is classified as an assault weapon and is banned from presence within that town or geographic area.

FFL transfer only means precisely that, and includes all LEOs, CIA, DIA, other government agencies.  IL FOID alone not accepted for transfer. Also please note, this gun IS an assault weapon under a number of assault weapons bans.  

It also is dovetailed for immediate installation of scopes, and can use HV ammunition with ease.  Effective range with good accuracy, depending on the ammunition, can reach 200 yards.  It also can use the "quite" or low noise ammunition or CB ammunition that several companies others market, for use on in-home target ranges indoors.

If a gun closer to a true free pistol is desired, please email for information about the Steyr, Pfuff, and Hammerli 150 and 160 pistols.  Of that group, the Pfuff is perhaps the best available, with the Steyr a very close second.  Some feel the reverse is true, with the Steyr being the best of all.  The Hammerli 150 and 160 are a close second best.  All are much more accurate than the current Morini and Pardini free pistols.

I want to sell my M91/30 Mosin Nagant. It's chambered in 7.62x54r which is a powerful, yet extremely inexpensive rifle round. As far as I can tell, all of the parts of the rifle are matching. The wood is fairly good, considering the age, and is auburn with a few various markings, most notably the etched russian character Ж near the sling and an Izhevesk manufacture print in a large star on the buttstock. Though it's only a Ishevsk made in 1943, I'd very much like the person I sell it to not irreparably damage by it trying to make some sort of fugly sporterized gun. Included are roughly 40 rounds of surplus/modern steel production, and 14 rounds of winchester white box JSP. Also contains the original issued sling, a dis-assembly tool, and a stripper clip.

Will consider trading + cash for a savage or ruger hunting rifle.

title: For Sale:  Pedersoli Harper's Ferry .58 Caliber Black Powder Pistol
postcontent:
Attention Black Powder enthusiasts, here is a replica of the famous Harpers Ferry Model 1807 Flint Lock pistol. This pistol was made in the 1960’s by Centennial Arms in Belgium before the company moved to Italy. These pistols are replicas of the US Model 1805 which were manufactured in the US Arsenal in Harpers Ferry VA between 1806 and 1808. A total of 4,096 of the original pistols were made and they were made in pairs with each pistol in the pair having the same serial number. This replica is in fine condition. It has brass furniture and a steel lock with a case color finish with an eagle motif and the US marking. The barrel is polished steel in the white and is .58 cal and the bore is rifled. The lock shows the evidence that it has been fired in the past. The stock has no cracks and retains 98% of its original finish. It has a few use bruises and scratches but it shows very well. All in all a very nice replica.
Pistol is in outstanding condition and has been well taken care of.
Barrel length: 10-1/16".
Overall length: 16-1/8".
Weight: 2.5 lbs.

title: For Sale:  AK Pistol in 5.56/.223: Century International M85 PV, New-in-the-Box
postcontent:
This is the “PV” Model 85 before they changed the current pistol to the “NP” to lower the price. 5 months ago this M85 PV pistol was set to retail at $626 and wholesale at $492. My price is $440 for quick sale. It comes NEW-IN-the-BOX, never handled by the public. However, I broke the factory seal to inspect and photograph it because there were reports that CIA (Century International Arms) AK’s were coming from Russia with crud under the handguard and crud in the barrels. I opened this box and ran a solvent-patch down the barrel, looked inside, checked under the handguard. This pistol came absolutely clean, externally and internally. I can find no fault, no criticism, plus it has the smoothest action you will find on any AK. Remember, AK’s are made from stamped parts, and it is their simplicity that gives them their legendary reliability. 

Other than my inspection, this pistol has not been out of the box. This M85 PV has the Yugo style muzzle break and comes with 3 (three) 30-round magazines, plus I throw in FREE, a brand new, packaged, ProMag AK-5, 30-round magazine in 5.56/.223 (Total = 4 magazines, each a different brand). (The “NP” series comes with only 2 magazines). Shipping is $30 to the lower 48, or actual cost, whichever is lower. 

Advice: Always, insert AK magazines with the bolt locked open. There is a technique for inserting AK magazines. First, practice with an empty magazine and open bolt/action until you get a feel for it. Don’t force it, use the magazine release. It’s quick and simple with one hand. 

This is a close-out, as old age is forcing retirement. I will no longer inventory any guns. My personal guns will be going too.  We are strictly a catalog-internet-wholesale-mail-order supplier of specialty & hard-to-find items for knowledgeable buyers.  None of our inventory or firearms are on display nor handled by the public.  All items are new in the box and are not on display to the public.  For locals, if you want to buy elsewhere, we will receive firearms free of charge if you order elsewhere (you pay your own shipping costs and background check).
